Xiuyi Jia 
E-mail: jiaxy@njust.edu.cn

School of Computer Science and Engineering      
Nanjing University of Science and Technology             
200 Xiaolingwei Street, Nanjing 210094, P.R. China

News

2019/06/10: 1 paper is accepted by Pattern Recognition Letters
2019/06/08: 1 paper is accepted by Information Sciences
2019/05/10: 2 papers are accepted by IJCAI'19 
2019/02/25: 1 paper is accepted by CVPR'19  


Research Intersets

Label-distribution learning
Multi-label learning
Three-way decisions and Granular computing
Natural language processing (NLP)
Weakly supervised learning (WSL)


Biography
Currently I am an Assistant Professor in Nanjing University of Science and Technology (NUST). 
I received my B.Sc. degree in Computer Science and Technology in Jun. 
2005 from Chongqing University, and my Ph.D. degree in Computer Science and Technology in Jun. 
2011 from Nanjing University. I spent one year (from Sep. 2008 to Sep. 2009) as a visiting graduate research student in Department of Computer Science, University of Regina, Canada. I studied with Professor Yiyu Yao.
